76561198001194174,Recommended,321960,19550634,"Posted: 7 December, 2015",all,Balgore,"Despite all the negative reviews and glitches/problems people reported, I took a chance on this game while it was on sale, and I am also a huge fan of the series, primarily HOMM 3.It doesn't have as many race choices as H3, but I knew that going into it.  It does however have a lot of unit and creature variety, and enough differing map monsters that there are a variety of fights to be had which offer many unique battles and cool unit abilities/specializations that add some depth to the tactics.Spells seem OP, but hey, they always were (blind I'm looking at you).  This is def. better than H6, and the levelling up system is improved.Note that so far I have played only the single player campaign, and have no interest in multiplayer, nor have I tried it.  It may or may not work, I don't know, but as far as all other reported glitches/problems/crashes reported, so far I have not experienced any of that, so that is good, and their latest patch does seem to have fixed a lot of the reported problems.The cinematics sucks, the story is so-so, but as long as you know that going into it you won't be disappointed.  Playing the game is what's fun.  I would love many more map options for single player scenario, as that is what kept me playing H3 for years and years (and still to this day), there are only a few choices at the current time, which kinda blows.  But the campaign offers a long enough game play experience to make this worth it, especially when it's on sale anyway.If you aren't a fan of the series, start with H3 as it's cheaper, and ultimately still the better game, and decide if you like this style of game before going for the full pop of this title."
