76561198045315388,Not Recommended,321960,18387671,"Posted: 8 October, 2015",all,Star Cake,"Disliked it. Simple as that. In all the years I have used Steam, this was the first time ever I asked for a refund. The game is very pricey, and feels unfinished. The graphics are very bland and uninspired, the combat sounds are awful, the music isn't good (something HOMM serie always got right), the 3D models on the main campaign table look really ugly and unfinished, and there are no animations for them. The game as a whole just felt really boring.Now a bit more personal; I disliked the factions and their creature distribution. I don't know why they had to make dungeon associated with dark elves and sylvan associated with elves. Just look at HOMM 2 and 3 titles and you'll see that those two factions were a lot more inspired. Some units design as a whole are terrible. I don't know, it just feels like the game was rushed, they threw everything inside a big cauldron, mixed it in a senseless manner and released the product for us to buy. Everything just feels very disconnected.The building tree UI is also bad. Looks very confusing and the townscreens could've been MUCH better. HOMM 2 and 3 townscreens were much more appealing and charming than what we got here, and they are 90's games. We are in 2015.If this game was maybe a 20 USD title, sure, but not for the current price. Overall it just feels like a very boring game and I would wait to buy it on a 75% discount weekend or something."
